def: Sottish; foolish; stupid; dull. [Obs.] "Rich, but sot."Marston.
More than once; again and again; indefinitely.
Quality or state of being weasy; full feeding; sensualindulgence. [Obs.] Joye.
The trade of mercers; the goods in which a mercer deals.
Of a pertaining to observation; consisting of, or containing,observations. Chalmers.
One who reasons or argues; as, a fair reasoner; a closereasoner; a logical reasoner.
A foot of two syllables, the first long and the second short,as in the Latin word ante, or the first accented and the secondunaccented, as in the English word motion; a choreus.
To put under a ban. [R.] Barlow.
